{"nodes":[{"content":"Deploy Windows To Go in your organization (Windows 10)","pos":[11,65]},{"content":"This topic helps you to deploy Windows To Go in your organization.","pos":[79,145]},{"content":"Deploy Windows To Go in your organization","pos":[369,410]},{"content":"Applies to","pos":[415,425]},{"content":"Windows 10","pos":[433,443]},{"content":"This topic helps you to deploy Windows To Go in your organization.","pos":[445,511]},{"content":"Before you begin deployment, make sure that you have reviewed the topics <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows To Go: feature overview<ept id=\"p1\">](../plan/windows-to-go-overview.md)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Prepare your organization for Windows To Go<ept id=\"p2\">](../plan/prepare-your-organization-for-windows-to-go.md)</ept> to ensure that you have the correct hardware and are prepared to complete the deployment.","pos":[512,849]},{"content":"You can then use the steps in this topic to start your Windows To Go deployment.","pos":[850,930]},{"content":"Note","pos":[934,938]},{"content":"This topic includes sample Windows PowerShell cmdlets that you can use to automate some of the procedures described.","pos":[943,1059]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Using Cmdlets<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=230693)</ept>.","pos":[1060,1151]},{"content":"Deployment tips","pos":[1159,1174]},{"content":"The following is a list of items that you should be aware of before you start the deployment process:","pos":[1177,1278]},{"content":"Only use recommended USB drives for Windows To Go.","pos":[1284,1334]},{"content":"Use of other drives is not supported.","pos":[1335,1372]},{"content":"Check the list at <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows To Go: feature overview<ept id=\"p1\">](../plan/windows-to-go-overview.md)</ept> for the latest USB drives certified for use as Windows To Go drives.","pos":[1373,1528]},{"content":"After you provision a new workspace, always eject a Windows To Go drive using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Safely Remove Hardware and Eject Media<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> control that can be found in the notification area or in Windows Explorer.","pos":[1534,1733]},{"content":"Removing the drive from the USB port without ejecting it first can cause the drive to become corrupted.","pos":[1734,1837]},{"content":"When running a Windows To Go workspace, always shutdown the workspace before unplugging the drive.","pos":[1843,1941]},{"content":"System Center 2012 Configuration Manager SP1 and later includes support for user self-provisioning of Windows To Go drives.","pos":[1947,2070]},{"content":"You can download Configuration Manager for evaluation from the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft TechNet Evaluation Center<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=618746)</ept>.","pos":[2071,2221]},{"content":"For more information on this deployment option, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to Provision Windows To Go in Configuration Manager<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619148)</ept>.","pos":[2222,2381]},{"content":"If you are planning on using a USB drive duplicator to duplicate Windows To Go drives, do not configure offline domain join or BitLocker on the drive.","pos":[2387,2537]},{"content":"Basic deployment steps","pos":[2542,2564]},{"content":"Unless you are using a customized operating system image, your initial Windows To Go workspace will not be domain joined and will not contain applications.","pos":[2567,2722]},{"content":"This is exactly like a new installation of Windows on a desktop or laptop computer.","pos":[2723,2806]},{"content":"When planning your deployment, you should develop methods to join Windows to Go drives to the domain and install the standard applications that users in your organization require.","pos":[2807,2986]},{"content":"These methods probably will be similar to the ones used for setting up desktop and laptop computers with domain privileges and applications.","pos":[2987,3127]},{"content":"This section describes the instructions for creating the correct disk layout on the USB drive, applying the operating system image and the core Windows To Go specific configurations to the drive.","pos":[3128,3323]},{"content":"The following steps are used in both small-scale and large-scale Windows To Go deployment scenarios.","pos":[3324,3424]},{"content":"Completing these steps will give you a generic Windows To Go drive that can be distributed to your users and then customized for their usage as needed.","pos":[3426,3577]},{"content":"This drive is also appropriate for use with USB drive duplicators.","pos":[3578,3644]},{"content":"Your specific deployment scenarios will involve more than just these basic steps but these additional deployment considerations are similar to traditional PC deployment and can be incorporated into your Windows To Go deployment plan.","pos":[3645,3878]},{"content":"For additional information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Deployment Options<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619149)</ept>.","pos":[3879,3989]},{"content":"Warning","pos":[3993,4000]},{"content":"If you are planning to use the generic Windows To Go drive as the master drive in a USB duplicator, the drive should not be booted.","pos":[4005,4136]},{"content":"If the drive has been booted inadvertently it should be reprovisioned prior to duplication.","pos":[4137,4228]},{"content":"Create the Windows To Go workspace","pos":[4237,4271]},{"content":"In this step we are creating the operating system image that will be used on the Windows To Go drives.","pos":[4273,4375]},{"content":"You can use the Windows To Go Creator Wizard or you can <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>do this manually<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619174)</ept> using a combination of Windows PowerShell and command-line tools.","pos":[4376,4565]},{"content":"Warning","pos":[4569,4576]},{"content":"The preferred method for creating a single Windows To Go drive is to use the Windows To Go Creator Wizard included in Windows 10 Enterprise and Windows 10 Education.","pos":[4581,4746]},{"content":"To create a Windows To Go workspace with the Windows To Go Creator Wizard","pos":[4753,4826]},{"content":"Sign into your Windows PC using an account with Administrator privileges.","pos":[4834,4907]},{"content":"Insert the USB drive that you want to use as your Windows To Go drive into your PC.","pos":[4913,4996]},{"content":"Verify that the .wim file location (which can be a network share, a DVD , or a USB drive) is accessible and that it contains a valid Windows 10 Enterprise or Windows 10 Education image that has been generalized using sysprep.","pos":[5002,5227]},{"content":"Many environments can use the same image for both Windows To Go and desktop deployments.","pos":[5228,5316]},{"pos":[5322,5609],"content":"**Note**  \nFor more information about .wim files, see [Windows System Image Manager (Windows SIM) Technical Reference](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619150). For more information about using sysprep, see [Sysprep Overview](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619151).","leadings":["","    "],"nodes":[{"content":"Note","pos":[2,6]},{"content":"For more information about .wim files, see [Windows System Image Manager (Windows SIM) Technical Reference](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619150). For more information about using sysprep, see [Sysprep Overview](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619151).","pos":[11,283],"nodes":[{"content":"For more information about .wim files, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows System Image Manager (Windows SIM) Technical Reference<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619150)</ept>.","pos":[0,157]},{"content":"For more information about using sysprep, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Sysprep Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619151)</ept>.","pos":[158,272]}]}]},{"content":"Using Cortana, search for <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows To Go<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and then press <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Enter<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[5622,5691]},{"content":"If the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>User Account Control<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box appears, confirm that the action it displays is what you want, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Yes<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[5692,5821]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows To Go Creator Wizard<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> opens.","pos":[5822,5865]},{"pos":[5871,6012],"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Choose the drive you want to use<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page select the drive that represents the USB drive you inserted previously, then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Next.<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>"},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Choose a Windows image<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Add Search Location<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and then navigate to the .wim file location and click select folder.","pos":[6018,6156]},{"content":"The wizard will display the installable images present in the folder; select the Windows 10 Enterprise or Windows 10 Education image you wish to use and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[6157,6330]},{"content":"(Optional) On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Set a BitLocker password (optional)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, you can select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Use BitLocker with my Windows To Go Workspace<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to encrypt your Windows To Go drive.","pos":[6336,6501]},{"content":"If you do not wish to encrypt the drive at this time, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Skip<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[6502,6571]},{"content":"If you decide you want to add BitLocker protection later, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Enable BitLocker protection for your Windows To Go drive<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=619152)</ept> for instructions.","pos":[6572,6759]},{"pos":[6765,6950],"content":"**Warning**  \nIf you are pla